#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:3
#: 26dea501616c45d5b78e106de78f6a6b
msgid "How to back up, restore, and migrate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:6
#: b8588b5a966b4f4eaab74f8b37728c54
msgid ""
"With Qubes, it’s easy and secure to back up and restore your whole "
"system, as well as to migrate between two physical machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:8
#: 815989cb365a4648844955faf25377f9
msgid ""
"These functions are integrated into the Qube Manager. There are also two "
"command-line tools available that perform the same functions: ``qvm-"
"backup`` and ``qvm-backup-restore``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:10
#: 5f2282731704490a8325864866844c09
msgid ""
"It’s extremely important to make regular backups of all the data you care"
" about. This is true of all computing, not just the use of Qubes. Data "
"loss can and does occur in myriad and unexpected ways. A standard "
"recommendation is to make backups at least weekly: three copies in two "
"different formats, one off-site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:13
#: 4b447d9de113422a9a7cb9e8ce2b53cd
msgid "Backing up changes to dom0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:16
#: 5de74c65c1144308b3cbed7022afc9b1
msgid ""
"When backing up dom0 using the Qubes backup tool (explained below), only "
"the home directory is backed up. Therefore, if there are files outside of"
" the home directory you wish to save, you should copy them into the home "
"directory prior to creating a backup. Here is an example of how to back "
"up Qubes config files and RPC policies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:27
#: f9ffb79f5f814bfc91374dad087b1b72
msgid ""
"To restore these files, move them from the restored directory in dom0’s "
"home back to their appropriate locations in ``/etc/``. Please note that "
"any packages installed via the package manager in dom0 will not be backed"
" up. Such packages will have to be reinstalled through the package "
"manager when restoring on a fresh installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:30
#: 341507139fe14b53b6d18f0f10525afb
msgid "Creating a backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:33
#: 34e139689b104e6e85d7e1721cf373ef
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Applications menu --> System Tools --> Backup "
"Qubes`. This brings up the **Qubes Backup VMs** window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:35
#: 233db3f06f5a45febe9471a9549f35ba
msgid ""
"Move the VMs that you want to back up to the right-hand **Selected** "
"column. VMs in the left-hand **Available** column will not be backed up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:37
#: 2684e0208171416bade5bd5aa9f3e6c6
msgid ""
"You may choose whether to compress backups by checking or unchecking the "
"**Compress the backup** box. Normally this should be left on unless you "
"have a specific reason otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:39
#: ee4062caa2f74551b48dd8218cdb1993
msgid "Once you have selected all desired VMs, click **Next**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:43
#: 450d7166cc35468aaa1554c703abbeaa
msgid "Select the destination for the backup:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:45
#: b36d6779065c4b28b8f886d741c6137a
msgid ""
"If you wish to send your backup to a (currently running) VM, select the "
"VM in the drop-down box next to **Target app qube**. If you wish to send "
"your backup to a :doc:`USB mass storage device </user/how-to-guides/how-"
"to-use-usb-devices>`, you can use the directory selection widget to mount"
" a connected device (under “Other locations” item on the left); or first "
"mount the device in a VM, then select the mount point inside that VM as "
"the backup destination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:47
#: 288a9526a51841a5b3e1b685b1a19827
msgid ""
"You must also specify a directory on the device or in the VM, or a "
"command to be executed in the VM as a destination for your backup. For "
"example, if you wish to send your backup to the ``~/backups`` folder in "
"the target VM, you would simply browse to it using the convenient "
"directory selection dialog (``...``) at the right. This destination "
"directory must already exist. If it does not exist, you must create it "
"manually prior to backing up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:49
#: 1dd1bd34c85240ee9c11a6961f6593ea
msgid ""
"By specifying the appropriate directory as the destination in a VM, it is"
" possible to send the backup directly to, e.g., a USB mass storage device"
" attached to the VM. Likewise, it is possible to enter any command as a "
"backup target by specifying the command as the destination in the VM. "
"This can be used to send your backup directly to, e.g., a remote server "
"using SSH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:51
#: 664a35875e724cdfa707ebdd1887f273
msgid ""
"**Note:** The supplied passphrase is used for **both** "
"encryption/decryption and integrity verification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:53
#: 225b5655d2924ed6b8a1a85ea6747b4f
msgid ""
"At this point, you may also choose whether to save your settings by "
"checking or unchecking the **Save settings as default backup profile** "
"box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:55
#: cc1ebb2fe278473eae6a568278eb8bde
msgid ""
"**Warning: Saving the settings will result in your backup passphrase "
"being saved in plaintext in dom0, so consider your threat model before "
"checking this box.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:59
#: 0a35ef8585a74603ae8be493c5a871ac
msgid ""
"You will now see the summary of VMs to be backed up. If there are any "
"issues preventing the backup, they will be listed here and the **Next** "
"button grayed out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:61
#: ec783730f7f04ac2b6cea823e2545ba9
msgid ""
"When you are ready, click **Next**. Qubes will proceed to create your "
"backup. Once the progress bar has completed, you may click **Finish**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:63
#: 0811efa06cef494ca3e4a8ded4db59b1
msgid ""
"Test restore your backup. Follow the `restore procedure <#restoring-"
"from-a-backup>`__, selecting **Verify backup integrity, do not restore "
"the data**. This step is optional but strongly recommended. A backup is "
"useless if you can’t restore your data from it, and you can’t be sure "
"that your backup is good until you try to restore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:68
#: f10ef1a25b6544f9938b963bbc673e0e
msgid "Restoring from a backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:71
#: 6c050575d6914f4399df0fc6ca2d6474
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Applications menu -> System Tools -> Restore "
"Backup`. This brings up the **Qubes Restore VMs** window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:73
#: 90f432d8fdc84be48c0ebd6b9d7f7009
msgid "Select the source location of the backup to be restored:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:75
#: e4f596d1a3b54c1d92d0413efb54cc5c
msgid ""
"If your backup is located on a :doc:`USB mass storage device </user/how-"
"to-guides/how-to-use-usb-devices>`, attach it first to another VM or "
"select ``sys-usb`` in the next item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:77
#: 029a9d3840de476bb277b37c07de7b55
msgid ""
"If your backup is located in a (currently running) VM, select the VM in "
"the drop-down box next to **app qube**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:80
#: 3a4e881d65144be08e5e0528056e7e4d
msgid ""
"You must also specify the directory and filename of the backup (or a "
"command to be executed in a VM) in the **Backup file** field. If you "
"followed the instructions in the previous section, “Creating a Backup,” "
"then your backup is most likely in the location you chose as the "
"destination in step 3. For example, if you had chosen the ``~/backups`` "
"directory of a VM as your destination in step 3, you would now select the"
" same VM and again browse to (using ``...``) the ``backups`` folder. Once"
" you’ve located the backup file, double-click it or select it and hit "
"**OK**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:82
#: 5fdfba40190c428f8c3c90e7e569553a
msgid "There are three options you may select when restoring from a backup:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:84
#: f163018df40342f9a907f7363e8cc173
msgid ""
"**ignore missing templates and net VMs**: If any of the VMs in your "
"backup depended upon a NetVM or template that is not present in (i.e., "
"“missing from”) the current system, checking this box will ignore the "
"fact that they are missing and restore the VMs anyway and set them to use"
" the default NetVM and system default template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:86
#: 81159d13b565415988927042719b5347
msgid ""
"**ignore username mismatch**: This option applies only to the restoration"
" of dom0’s home directory. If your backup was created on a Qubes system "
"which had a different dom0 username than the dom0 username of the current"
" system, then checking this box will ignore the mismatch between the two "
"usernames and proceed to restore the home directory anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:88
#: a4911faac42f40bdb4dcf979bad6c4bb
msgid ""
"**Verify backup integrity, do not restore the data**: This will scan the "
"backup file for corrupted data. However, it does not currently detect if "
"it is missing data as long as it is a correctly structured, non-corrupted"
" backup file. See `issue #3498 <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/3498>`__ for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:92
#: c4b4521b53544a9081c36ba93b3db159
msgid ""
"If your backup is encrypted, you must check the **Encrypted backup** box."
" If a passphrase was supplied during the creation of your backup "
"(regardless of whether it is encrypted), then you must supply it here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:94
#: 5ee23d3fe94342eeb27e998fe5e472a8
msgid ""
"**Note:** The passphrase which was supplied when the backup was created "
"is used for **both** encryption/decryption and integrity verification. If"
" the backup was not encrypted, the supplied passphrase is used only for "
"integrity verification. All backups made from a Qubes R4.0 system will be"
" encrypted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:98
#: eea76ff71f5c46ddacac188d9ad1b38d
msgid ""
"You will now see the summary of VMs to be restored. If there are any "
"issues preventing the restore, they will be listed here and the **Next** "
"button grayed out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:100
#: 3dd11a09515147a8bb5092721af88128
msgid ""
"When you are ready, click **Next**. Qubes will proceed to restore from "
"your backup. Once the progress bar has completed, you may click "
"**Finish**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:104
#: 4d14fad2572743cf90a780c5492456e7
msgid ""
"In case that applications are not shown, i.e. “No applications found”, "
"open the settings of the qube -> select :guilabel:`Applications`, click "
":guilabel:`Refresh applications`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:106
#: f6f83e3e5ab94cb6bb64406ab763b980
msgid ""
"When a restored application qube refreshes, the application lists will "
"open the template qubes on which it is based. In that case the template "
"qube should also be restored, if it is missing the default qube will be "
"assigned. The updated list of the installed software can be seen on the "
"left and adjusted accordingly to the user’s needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:108
#: 4ce4f9df60914d1db0490991d50e7826
msgid ""
"**Note:** When restoring from a dom0 backup, a new directory will be "
"created in the current dom0 home directory, and the contents from the "
"backup will be placed inside this new directory. This is intentional, as "
"it allows users to have explicit control over which files and settings "
"get applied in dom0. If the contents from the dom0 backup were instead to"
" overwrite the existing files in dom0’s home directory, unexpected and "
"undesired configuration changes could occur. However, if you do wish to "
"move all files from the dom0 backup out of the subdirectory into your "
"current dom0 home directory (overwriting any existing files in the "
"process), you may do so by following the instructions `here "
"<https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20192070/how-to-move-all-files-"
"including-hidden-files-into-parent-directory-via>`__. Just remember that "
"this can cause unexpected and undesired configuration changes in dom0, "
"depending on exactly which files you’re adding and replacing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:111
#: c1edb2735489401ba3db660843ad2a56
msgid "Emergency backup recovery without qubes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:114
#: e46bebb2d2bf4d1892915b7af6e03fc5
msgid ""
"The Qubes backup system has been designed with emergency disaster "
"recovery in mind. No special Qubes-specific tools are required to access "
"data backed up by Qubes. In the event a Qubes system is unavailable, you "
"can access your data on any GNU/Linux system with the following "
"procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:116
#: fb7b40fbe37048bba150f4a554f7835f
msgid "Refer to the following for emergency restore of a backup created on:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:130
#: b148d08525384bd3b69d2269639b1146
msgid "Migrating between two physical machines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:133
#: 9e106724aec44b1395941968927fda60
msgid ""
"In order to migrate your Qubes system from one physical machine to "
"another, simply follow the backup procedure on the old machine, `install "
"Qubes <https://www.qubes-os.org/downloads/>`__ on the new machine, and "
"follow the restoration procedure on the new machine. All of your settings"
" and data will be preserved!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:136
#: 1750e3145c2e4f8e8f2b7005586ee4a5
msgid "Choosing a backup passphrase"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:139
#: 0d0f4e7d701943eeb4be154f56e91458
msgid ""
"Here are some things to consider when selecting a passphrase for your "
"backups:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:141
#: f117e51e61914d4687c01109f1ac0409
msgid ""
"If you plan to store the backup for a long time or on third-party "
"servers, you should make sure to use a very long, high-entropy "
"passphrase. (Depending on the decryption passphrase you use for your "
"system drive, this may necessitate selecting a stronger passphrase. If "
"your system drive decryption passphrase is already sufficiently strong, "
"it may not.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:143
#: a86b113121894e29bf62692ddec69230
msgid ""
"An adversary who has access to your backups may try to substitute one "
"backup for another. For example, when you attempt to retrieve a recent "
"backup, the adversary may instead give you a very old backup containing a"
" compromised VM. If you’re concerned about this type of attack, you may "
"wish to use a different passphrase for each backup, e.g., by appending a "
"number or date to the passphrase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:145
#: efdd4d9975ec40f3b01948907a8b734e
msgid ""
"If you’re forced to enter your system drive decryption passphrase in "
"plain view of others (where it can be shoulder-surfed), then you may want"
" to use a different passphrase for your backups (even if your system "
"drive decryption passphrase is already maximally strong). On the other "
"hand, if you’re careful to avoid shoulder-surfing and/or have a "
"passphrase that’s difficult to detect via shoulder-surfing, then this may"
" not be a problem for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:150
#: 0b3e4af2df8b4a3c82d888c63016d8e8
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:153
#: bdabb45df22d4a87bc68246d9f870704
msgid ""
"For the technical details of the backup system, please refer to `this "
"thread <https://groups.google.com/d/topic/qubes-"
"devel/TQr_QcXIVww/discussion>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate.rst:155
#: 93b1323dbe4b43c7ab26c1319b67178e
msgid ""
"If working with symlinks, note the issues described in `this thread "
"<https://groups.google.com/d/topic/qubes-"
"users/EITd1kBHD30/discussion>`__."
msgstr ""

